f=Cybersecurity/bastion/custom/hardening-baselines/SKILL.md · in=Secure configuration baselines things business runs servers/OS, cloud services, endpoints (laptops), containers they ship locked down instead default-open. bastion defines baseline (from CIS Benchmarks), measures actual config against it, specs gaps; operator/ops applies hardening. · p=Defaults convenient, secure default install, unhardened container image, laptop disk encryption. defined baseline turns "is configured securely" measurable check, closes drift between "how set up" "how actually is." · wu=Provisioning a new server/service/endpoint/image., "Harden this," "config baseline," "is box secure," "CIS benchmark.", Baseline compliance scan cadence; after config changes. · st:/ Protocol=DEFINE (the baseline platform, CIS Benchmarks: OS, cloud service, container, endpoint dated, because platforms change) MEASURE (actual config baseline deviations) PRIORITIZE (deviations exploitability exposure) SPEC (bastion writes hardening; operator/ops applies IaC possible it's repeatable, manual) ENDPOINTS (laptops: disk encryption, screen lock, patch level, EDR human-device attack surface) RE-MEASURE (drift: config reverts insecure finding process gap). · in=**Baseline CIS, platform, dated.** CIS Benchmarks reference; platform's baseline carries as-of date (cloud/OS versions change volatility split, security edition). GRC CIS Controls pack catalog. **Measure, don't assume.** Actual config baseline produces deviations; "we hardened it" without measurement claim, fact (the fleet's evidence rule, infra edition). **Baselines apply IaC possible.** Hardening baked infrastructure-as-code repeatable drift-resistant; manual hardening decays. bastion specs it; ops/dev implement IaC. **Endpoints count.** Employee laptops infrastructure too: disk encryption, screen-lock, current patches, endpoint protection. compromised unhardened laptop common breach entry (cortex responds endpoint compromise). **bastion specs; operator/ops applies.** inversion bastion measures writes hardening, operator ops's gate applies real systems. **Drift finding.** Config reverts insecure manual change, un-updated image) process gap, surfaced warden, re-hardened scan. · of=`## Hardening: [platform/asset] — baseline: [CIS, as-of date] \· Deviations: [setting \· current \· baseline \· exploitability \· exposure] \· Endpoints: [disk-encryption \· lock \· patch level \· EDR] (if applicable) \· Fix spec → [operator / ops IaC] (bastion measures, doesn't apply) \· Drift: [reverted settings → process-gap finding] \· Risks → warden` · pr=**Baseline CIS, platform, dated** versions change., **Measure, don't assume** "hardened" needs evidence., **Apply IaC** repeatable, drift-resistant; manual decays., **Endpoints infrastructure** laptops common entry point., **bastion specs; operator/ops applies** inversion., **Drift process-gap finding** per-scan re-fix. · f=CIS tooling apply CIS Benchmark checklist manually platform, prioritized high-exploitability settings, labeled manual., IaC hardening manual documented re-measured cadence (drift-prone, flagged); recommend IaC dev/ops. · b:with Other Skills=**cloud-posture** (sibling): cloud control-plane config; host/OS/endpoint/container config., **infra-vuln-management** (sibling): patching hardening dimension) config, CVEs., **ops (Engineering)**: applies hardening gate/IaC; ops maintenance-hygiene patches, bastion baselines config., **cortex**: endpoint compromise triggers response; **warden**: deviations drift register risks.